          <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterCharacters('offensive')">The Order</button>
        </div>

        <!-- Book 1 Characters -->
        <article id="thomas" class="character-card reveal delay-1" data-book="book1" data-network="defensive">
          <div class="character-header">
            <div>
              <h2>Thomas of Eltville</h2>
              <p class="character-title">Scribe & Reluctant Genesis Carrier</p>
              <div class="character-meta">
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Book</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Book 1 (1347 CE)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Generation</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Gen 90</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Age</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">28</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Activation Level</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Full Cascade</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="network-badge defensive">Genesis Protocol</span>
          </div>

          <div class="character-body">
            <p>
              Thomas begins as an ordinary scribe working for the Archbishop of Mainz. He's educated
              but not brilliant, devout but questioning, content with his predictable life copying
              manuscripts and recording church business. When his mentor Brother Hamo thrusts the iron key
              into his hands moments before dying, Thomas experiences his first genetic memory
              cascade: 2,500 years of accumulated knowledge flooding his consciousness in seconds.
            </p>
            <p>
              His journey is one of reluctant heroism. Thomas doesn't want to be special. He wants
              his quiet scribe life back. But as genetic memory activations intensify, he realizes
              he's Generation 90 in an unbroken defensive network bloodline. The "hallucinations"
              are real—Egyptian medical procedures, Greek mathematics, Roman engineering—all passed
              through DNA methylation patterns designed by Nefertari herself.
            </p>
            <p>
              Thomas represents the defensive network's core dilemma: what do you do with knowledge
              you didn't ask for, inherited from ancestors you've never met, that makes you a target
              for forces you don't understand? His character arc explores consent, responsibility,
              and whether genetic inheritance constitutes destiny or merely predisposition.
            </p>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Key Quote</h3>
              <div class="quote-block">
                "Then we use the network's own preservation methods against them. Encode the complete
                Protocol into manuscripts using their cipher. Distribute copies to monasteries and
                libraries across Europe—so many, in so many places, that destroying all of them becomes
                impossible. Hide the evidence in plain sight using the same methods they used to preserve
                knowledge across collapses."
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Relationships</h3>
              <div class="relationships-list">
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Margarethe</strong> — Co-conspirator and eventual romantic
                  partner. She recognizes his genetic activation because her bloodline was engineered
                  by the Order—making their relationship a literal genetic experiment spanning 2,500
                  years.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Brother Hamo</strong> — Thomas's mentor and the dying monk who passes the iron key.
                  Hamo is murdered by the Order's Gray Robes while protecting Wilhelm's network secrets.
                  He deliberately gives the key to Thomas, believing in the gift Wilhelm saw in him.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Heinrich</strong> — Margarethe's father, a merchant tortured and killed
                  by Brother Anselm for information about Wilhelm's network. His death drives Margarethe
                  to join Thomas in exposing the Order.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Wilhelm (Grandfather)</strong> — Thomas's grandfather who was part of the
                  defensive network. Wilhelm taught Thomas to see patterns in manuscripts before dying
                  under mysterious circumstances. His teachings and the iron key he left behind set
                  Thomas on his journey.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Defining Moments</h3>
              <ul class="moments-list">
                <li>Receives the iron key from dying Brother Hamo, beginning his journey into the conspiracy</li>
                <li>Gathers all seven fragments of the Genesis Protocol with Margarethe and Maria through blood memory access in hidden libraries across Europe</li>
                <li>Encodes the complete Protocol into manuscript copies and distributes them across Europe, making the knowledge impossible to destroy</li>
                <li>Sends letters to network members exposing the corruption, forcing them to choose between continued service or rebellion</li>
                <li>Settles in a Welsh village to teach children pattern recognition, choosing patient building over grand gestures</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article id="margarethe" class="character-card reveal delay-1" data-book="book1" data-network="defensive">
          <div class="character-header">
            <div>
              <h2>Margarethe</h2>
              <p class="character-title">Cloth Merchant & Cipher Keeper</p>
              <div class="character-meta">
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Book</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Book 1 (1347 CE)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Generation</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Gen 64 (Defensive lineage)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Age</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">~25</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Role</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Memory Keeper</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="network-badge defensive">Defensive Network</span>
          </div>

          <div class="character-body">
            <p>
              Margarethe is a cloth merchant whose scholar father Heinrich was tortured to death by the Order
              when she was young. Despite being illiterate—or perhaps because of it—she possesses an
              extraordinary memory. Her father taught her the cipher network's secrets through visual patterns
              and memorization, making her a "library that cannot burn." She carries locations, methodologies,
              and network knowledge in her mind without needing written records.
            </p>
            <p>
              Unlike Thomas, who inherited defensive bloodline traits through genetics, Margarethe earned her
              knowledge through brutal necessity. She's a skilled fighter, survivor, and teacher—transforming
              seamlessly between merchant, protector, and cipher instructor. Her inability to read forces her
              to develop pattern recognition through memory alone, making her approach to the cipher fundamentally
              different from Thomas's scholarly analysis.
            </p>
            <p>
              Her character explores knowledge preservation through non-traditional means. In a world where the
              written word can be burned and scholars can be killed, Margarethe represents oral tradition and
              embodied knowledge. She's proof that the defensive network's mission—preserving knowledge across
              collapse—doesn't require literacy, only dedication and memory.
            </p>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Key Quote</h3>
              <div class="quote-block">
                "My father taught me to be the library that cannot burn. They tortured him, killed him,
                destroyed his manuscripts. But they couldn't destroy what lives in my memory. Every
                location, every cipher, every name—I carry it all. And I will teach others to carry
                it too."
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Relationships</h3>
              <div class="relationships-list">
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Thomas of Eltville</strong> — She saves him from the Order's pursuit and
                  becomes his teacher and protector. Their partnership evolves from necessity to genuine
                  connection as they decipher the cipher together.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Heinrich the Scholar</strong> — Her father, tortured to death by the Order
                  when she was young. He taught her everything through memory and visual patterns,
                  knowing written knowledge could be destroyed. His death drives her mission to preserve
                  the network's secrets.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Brother Anselm</strong> — The Order operative who hunts them. He sees
                  Margarethe as a dangerous carrier of forbidden knowledge that must be eliminated
                  before she can teach others.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Defining Moments</h3>
              <ul class="moments-list">
                <li>Rescues Thomas from Order pursuers in Mainz using her fighting skills and knowledge of the city</li>
                <li>Teaches Thomas the cipher system her father taught her through patient instruction and visual demonstration</li>
                <li>Navigates the market while evading Order surveillance, transforming seamlessly into her merchant persona</li>
                <li>Uses her memorized knowledge to guide them to hidden network contacts and safe locations</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article id="wilhelm" class="character-card reveal delay-1" data-book="book1" data-network="defensive">
          <div class="character-header">
            <div>
              <h2>Wilhelm von Eltville</h2>
              <p class="character-title">Cipher Master & Network Member</p>
              <div class="character-meta">
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Book</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Book 1 (Deceased 1347)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Generation</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Gen 62 (Defensive lineage)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Age at Death</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">68</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Role</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Thomas's Grandfather, Key Holder</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="network-badge defensive">Defensive Network</span>
          </div>

          <div class="character-body">
            <p>
              Wilhelm von Eltville was Thomas's grandfather and a cipher master in the defensive network.
              He died in 1347, just before the story begins, but his legacy shapes everything Thomas
              becomes. Wilhelm spent decades studying the cipher system, holding one of the seven bronze
              keys (the Iron Key, "Eye that Sees") that reveals locations and patterns within the network.
            </p>
            <p>
              As a network member, Wilhelm understood that knowledge preservation required sacrifice and
              vigilance. He trained in pattern recognition and taught what he could to his family, knowing
              the Order would eventually come for them. His death passes the iron key to Thomas, making
              his grandson the next generation's carrier—whether Thomas wants that burden or not.
            </p>
            <p>
              Wilhelm represents the defensive network's idealism: that knowledge should be preserved and
              distributed freely, that humanity can learn from collapse patterns and prevent future
              catastrophes. His life's work was gathering cipher fragments and protecting the network's
              secrets from Order interference. His death at the story's beginning sets Thomas on the path
              to continuing that mission.
            </p>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Key Quote</h3>
              <div class="quote-block">
                "The cipher is not just knowledge—it's responsibility. Whoever carries the keys must
                understand: we preserve not for power, but for survival. When the next collapse comes,
                the world will need what we've protected. Guard it well, Thomas."
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Relationships</h3>
              <div class="relationships-list">
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Thomas of Eltville</strong> — His grandson and heir. Wilhelm's death passes
                  the iron key to Thomas, thrusting him into the network's world. Thomas carries both
                  his grandfather's genetic traits (pattern recognition) and his mission.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>The Defensive Network</strong> — A respected cipher master who held one of
                  the seven original keys. His death represents a loss of knowledge and experience that
                  the network can ill afford during the Black Death's chaos.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>The Order</strong> — They likely caused or hastened Wilhelm's death, seeing
                  him as a dangerous keeper of forbidden knowledge. His passing removes a significant
                  obstacle to their control operations.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Key Moments (Pre-Story)</h3>
              <ul class="moments-list">
                <li>Taught young Thomas to see patterns in manuscripts, recognizing his grandson had "his grandmother's eyes"</li>
                <li>On his deathbed, warned Thomas about the Order: "They have built something that outlives any man—a pattern that feeds on disaster"</li>
                <li>Gave Thomas the strategy to fight the Order: "Break the secrecy—scatter their knowledge like seed on wind"</li>
                <li>Died under mysterious circumstances (officially "fell from his horse") after a stranger with the Order's key symbol visited</li>
                <li>Arranged for Brother Hamo to pass the iron key to Thomas when the time came</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Book 2 Characters -->
        <article id="sarah" class="character-card reveal delay-1" data-book="book2" data-network="defensive">
          <div class="character-header">
            <div>
              <h2>Dr. Sarah Chen</h2>
              <p class="character-title">Genetic Researcher & Modern Genesis Carrier</p>
              <div class="character-meta">
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Book</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Book 2 (2017-2025 CE)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Generation</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Gen 82</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Age</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">32</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Activation Level</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Spontaneous Cascade</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="network-badge defensive">Genesis Protocol</span>
          </div>

          <div class="character-body">
            <p>
              Sarah is a genetic researcher at GenVault Corporation in Boston when she discovers
              an impossible pattern: medieval manuscript marginalia from the 14th century contains
              genetic knowledge that shouldn't exist. By overlaying the colored dots from plague-era
              manuscripts onto modern genomic maps, she finds perfect alignment with populations that
              survived the Black Death—knowledge created 700 years before modern genetics existed.
            </p>
            <p>
              Unlike Thomas, who lived in an era accepting of divine mysteries, Sarah is a scientist
              requiring mechanistic explanations. Her genetic memory activations terrify her precisely
              because they shouldn't be possible. She spends weeks trying to explain them through
              neurological disorders, stress-induced hallucinations, anything except the truth: she's
              carrying 3,200 years of accumulated knowledge in her DNA.
            </p>
            <p>
              Her character represents the defensive network in the genomic age. Pattern recognition
              is no longer metaphorical—she can literally sequence the genetic markers Nefertari
              designed. The defensive methodology isn't hidden in art or scripture anymore—it's
              written in ATCG base pairs, ready to be decoded, distributed, and potentially edited
              by CRISPR technology.
            </p>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Key Quote</h3>
              <div class="quote-block">
                "She was a product. A designed outcome. Twelve generations of controlled breeding had
                produced her the way you'd breed dogs for specific traits."
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Relationships</h3>
              <div class="relationships-list">
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Dr. James Morrison</strong> — Head of GenVault's Research Division and
                  Sarah's captor. Morrison reveals the breeding program and tries to convince Sarah
                  that controlled genetic optimization is humanity's only path to survival.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Dr. Otto Aris</strong> — Sarah's mentor at GenVault who warns her she's
                  being watched. He helps her understand the medieval cipher patterns before
                  mysteriously disappearing.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>David Chen</strong> — Sarah's cousin, raised together by Aunt Lin. David
                  helps Sarah distribute her expose documents and provides safe houses during her
                  escape from GenVault.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Dr. Evelyn Marsh</strong> — Reclusive historian who spent forty years
                  researching the cipher. Marsh reveals Sarah's true lineage and teaches her
                  how to access the genetic memories intentionally.
                </div>
                <div class="relationship-item">
                  <strong>Tausret (ancestral)</strong> — Sarah experiences her memories during
                  full cascades. She's the 82nd-generation descendant of Tausret (Pharaoh Twosret),
                  who became the first "living key" carrier in 1177 BCE.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Defining Moments</h3>
              <ul class="moments-list">
                <li>Discovers medieval manuscript marginalia contains genetic knowledge 700 years before modern genetics existed</li>
                <li>Warned by Dr. Otto Aris that GenVault is watching her, beginning her paranoia and investigation</li>
                <li>Captured by GenVault and shown her complete family tree with breeding annotations—realizes her parents' marriage was arranged</li>
                <li>Writes 40,000-word expose in Vermont cabin with David's help, preparing to release GenVault's secrets</li>
                <li>Discovers she's descended from Maria (Book 1) through her youngest son Rafael, who moved to Guangdong—the Chen bloodline traces back twelve generations</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article id="marcus" class="character-card reveal delay-1" data-book="book2" data-network="order">
          <div class="character-header">
            <div>
              <h2>Marcus Webb</h2>
              <p class="character-title">GenVault VP & Network Defector</p>
              <div class="character-meta">
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Book</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Book 2 (2018-2025 CE)</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Generation</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Order Operative</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Role</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">VP of Research Operations</span>
                </div>
                <div class="character-meta-item">
                  <span class="meta-label">Arc</span>
                  <span class="meta-value">Antagonist → Defector</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <span class="network-badge order">The Order</span>
          </div>

          <div class="character-body">
            <p>
              Marcus Webb is GenVault's VP of Research Operations—one of the network's trusted
              operatives responsible for hunting Sarah Chen when she discovers the medieval cipher
              patterns. He appears in Chapter 1 as the face of GenVault's power: expensive suit at
              midnight, security guards at his back, patient predatory smile as he corners Sarah
              in the lab.
            </p>
            <p>
              But Marcus represents something crucial to Book 2's themes: the Order operative who
              believes in the mission until forced to see its true cost. He coordinates THRESHOLD
              operations from London Heathrow (hub THRESH-22), genuinely believing the network's
              genetic optimization program serves humanity's survival during coming collapse.
            </p>
            <p>
              When Otto Aris distributes historical documentation showing the network corrupted its
              founding defensive purpose, Marcus independently verifies the evidence. In Chapter 7,
              he becomes one of seven hub coordinators who publicly refuse to participate in
              THRESHOLD deployment—choosing humanity over conspiracy when forced to consciously
              acknowledge what he's actually doing.
            </p>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Key Quote</h3>
              <div class="quote-block">
                "The historical evidence is authenticated. I verified independently. The network
                corrupted its founding purpose. I refuse to serve this corruption. Withdrawing from
                THRESHOLD coordination."
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="character-section">
              <h3>Defining Moments</h3>
              <ul class="moments-list">
                <li>Corners Sarah Chen in GenVault lab at midnight with security guards, beginning her hunt</li>
                <li>Coordinates THRESHOLD operations as hub coordinator for London Heathrow (THRESH-22)</li>
                <li>Reads Otto Aris's historical documentation and independently verifies the evidence of network corruption</li>
